BHEKI Sithole was a good person who loved to have fun and enjoy himself. The 33-year-old man went for a braai in Cullinan, Tshwane, on Sunday, 10 July, at about 5.30pm. When he got back that night, he went to Monaco Tavern at SNS in Mamelodi East where he was later killed. This is according to Bheki’s brother Thabo (37). “We were shocked when we got a call on Monday morning, saying that Bheki had been killed at a tavern,” said Thabo. He said his brother was a good man and didn’t have enemies. “This is so heartbreaking. We want justice to be served,” he said. ALSO READ | Residents gatvol of mlungu PHARA Thabo said his brother, who was a motor mechanic, survived by fixing cars at their home in Extension 4, Mamelodi East. “We were very close. We were like twins and shared everything. I will really miss him,” he said. Captain Augustinah Selepe said the cops in Tshwane launched a manhunt after a 33-year-old man was shot at Monaco Tavern in Mamelodi East on Monday, 11 July, at about 1am. ALSO READ | Olwethu dies after funeral! “It’s alleged that three unknown armed suspects wearing balaclavas arrived at the tavern and fired shots in the air and people dispersed. They approached the deceased and shot him in the head. The motive is unknown at this stage. Police are investigating a case of murder,” said Selepe.